==后续==
奥巴马之后称与拉什竞选失败是他的一个低谷<ref name="nyt" />，并承认了自己的狂妄自大<ref name="usatoday" />。不过，许多分析认为奥巴马的这一失败让他认识到自己的不足，进而在2004年的伊利诺伊州联邦参议员选举以及2008年美国总统选举中获得胜利<ref name="nyt" /><ref name="salon">{{cite news |url=http://www.salon.com/2007/02/12/obama_natural/ |title=How Obama learned to be a natural |first=Edward |last=McClelland |work=Salon.com |date=2007-02-12 |accessdate=2013-10-18 |archivedate=2012-10-22 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022022956/http://www.salon.com/2007/02/12/obama_natural/ }}</ref><ref name="usatoday">{{cite news |url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/politics/2007-10-24-3157940059_x.htm |title=Obama learned from failed Congress run |newspaper=USA Today |date=2007-10-24 |accessdate=2013-10-18 |first=Christopher |last=Wills |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130127005857/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/politics/2007-10-24-3157940059_x.htm |archivedate=2013-01-27 }}</ref>。奥巴马曾被认为是个在政策方面思维僵化的书呆子，他用这一次选举的经历来磨练自己与选民打交道的能力<ref name="nyt" />。据奥巴马早期的支持者，芝加哥市议员{{link-en|托尼·普里克温克|Toni Preckwinkle}}所说，奥巴马“在那次竞选后仔细地审视了自己，成为一个更优秀的活动家，在竞选过程中更加放松”<ref name="usatoday"/>。他在竞选中投入更大的努力，聘请[[大卫·阿克塞尔罗德|大卫·阿克塞尔罗德]]担任自己的首席政治战略家<ref name="nyt" />。并且他在伊利诺伊州参议院的工作也更加努力，改善了自己在立法领域所获得的成绩<ref name="salon"/>。

2004年，奥巴马在[[民主党全国大会|民主党全国大会]]上发表主题演讲<ref>{{cite news |author=Bernstein, David |date=2007-06 |title=The Speech |magazine=Chicago Magazine |archivedate=2013-10-10 |url=http://www.chicagomag.com/Chicago-Magazine/June-2007/The-Speech/ |accessdate=2013-10-18 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131010065213/http://www.chicagomag.com/Chicago-Magazine/June-2007/The-Speech/ }}</ref>。这次演讲后，一些政治评论家预测他将来有望成为总统候选人<ref name="status">{{cite news |date=2004-08-02 |title=Star Power. Showtime: Some are on the rise; others have long been fixtures in the firmament. A galaxy of bright Democratic lights |work=Newsweek |pages=48-51 |url=http://www.newsweek.com/id/54728/output/print |deadurl=no |accessdate=2013-10-18 |archivedate=2013-10-10 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131010065213/http://www.chicagomag.com/Chicago-Magazine/June-2007/The-Speech/ }}</ref>。同年当选联邦参议员后，媒体对奥巴马将来的计划出现了许多猜测。2007年2月，奥巴马宣布自己有意争夺2008年民主党总统候选人提名<ref name="ChicagoTribune_Pearson_20070210">{{cite news |archivedate=2013-07-30 |deadurl=no |url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/politics/chi-070210obama-pearson1-story,0,3768114.story |title=Obama: I'm running for president |work=Chicago Tribune |author=Pearson, Rick |coauthors=Long, Ray |date=2007-02-10 |accessdate=2013-10-18 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130730233639/http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/politics/chi-070210obama-pearson1-story%2C0%2C3768114.story }}</ref><ref name="BBC20070210">{{cite news |title=Obama Launches Presidential Bid |date=2007-02-10 |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/6349081.stm |publisher=BBC News Online |accessdate=2013-10-18 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130808141207/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/6349081.stm |deadurl=no |archivedate=2013-08-08 }}</ref>，并以美国历史上最微弱的差距击败[[希拉里·罗德姆·克林顿|希拉里·罗德姆·克林顿]]成功获得提名<ref>{{cite news |last=Nagourney |first=Adam |first2=Jeff |last2=Zeleny |title=Clinton to End Bid and Endorse Obama |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/06/05/us/politics/04cnd-campaign.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=2008-06-05 |accessdate=2013-10-18 |archivedate=2013-05-10 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130510124813/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/06/05/us/politics/04cnd-campaign.html }}</ref>，之后成功地在普选中击败同为联邦参议员的[[約翰·麥凱恩|約翰·麥凱恩]]当选为美国总统<ref>{{cite news |archivedate=2013-08-25 |deadurl=no |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/us_elections_2008/7709978.stm |title=Obama wins historic US election |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130825024717/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/us_elections_2008/7709978.stm |publisher=BBC News Online |date=2008-11-05 |accessdate=2013-10-18 }}</ref>。

